According to Article 6(1) of the GDPR:

"Processing shall be lawful only if and to the extent that at least one of the following applies:
(a) the data subject has given consent to the processing of his or her personal data for one or more specific purposes;
(b) processing is necessary for the performance of a contract to which the data subject is party or in order to take steps at the request of the data subject prior to entering into a contract;

Processing is necessary for compliance with a legal obligation to which the controller is subject;

The data subject has given explicit consent to the processing of those personal data for one or more specified purposes, in the context of the employment, where the processor is a natural person who is a member of an employer's group which offers goods or services to members who are natural persons, is acting in the context of such employment, consisting of the processing of those members' personal data as a privilege benefit essential in that specific closed system.
"
